-- Bollard Says ‘Comfortable’ With the Market View on New Zealand Rate Pause
-- B y   T r a c y   W i t h e r s
-- 2012-01-27T00:23:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/bollard-says-comfortable-with-the-market-view-on-new-zealand-rate-pause.html
New Zealand central bank Governor
Alan Bollard said he is “comfortable” with the current market
view that the official cash rate won’t rise or fall over the
next year. Bollard commented during a speech to business leaders
in Christchurch today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tracy Withers at 
 twithers@bloomberg.net  